"Yes, sir. They should be on their way now; we gave them time to pack food from the mess hall." At 05:00, Exodus platoon gathered at the vehicle yard. Captain肖 stood on a crate and began to speak.
"We are heading to the I-131 frontline operations base, 50 miles outside of Ianlos City. We will support the ongoing siege operation and then attack Ianlos City, clearing out the rebels there. We will use this as our base to advance into the mountains," Captain肖 explained. "Take your squad and prepare to depart."
The platoon dispersed, and each squad, under the leadership of their squad leader, boarded a tank. Kollen climbed onto a tank at the front of the convoy and sat with Nimitz, Cress, and two new recruits. Kollen remembered they had arrived just a few days ago, but he didn't know much about them. He sat on the edge of the tank with his legs dangling, adjusting his backpack and radio equipment, connecting it to his headset and throat microphone.
"Hey, Kollen, is Harris still keeping Snowball?" Nimitz asked after they had settled in.
"You mean the chicken he stole?" Kollen recalled the incident when they had stolen a chicken from the farm that morning. "Exactly, I'm sure of it."
Koren looked toward another tank and saw Harris and his squad. He faintly saw a chick peering around from behind Harris's backpack.
"Right, he's still keeping that chicken," Koren replied as the tank turret hatch creaked open and the tank commander appeared in front of them.
"All tanks are moving out," the commander said calmly and clearly into his earpiece. The tanks of the armored platoon and the Schreck armored cars rumbled forward with their engines. Koren's Cronostan tank released the brakes and moved forward, joining the formation. The tanks formed a wedge formation as they crossed the Itanian plain. The winter blizzard had frozen the wetlands and forests, but the mud still remained.
After about an hour, a new recruit (Koren remembered his name was Orson) asked, "Lieutenant, have you been on the front lines since the war started?"
"Yes, since the Firestorm Operation began," Koren replied. "We thought the fighting would be over in a few weeks, but... we underestimated them."
"More than just underestimated." Nimitch also joined the conversation. "Their weapons and numbers exceeded our expectations. They shot down the UFS Revenant in the first two weeks and Erebus last month. Damn it, we should have been able to see it on the road."
"Well, I will bravely fight for the Federation." Osin said firmly, "I won't be scared by those terrorists."
"You say that now, but as far as I can see, most of the new recruits like you who just reached adulthood run for cover as soon as they hear gunshots," Kres said.
"We'll see about that," Kollen said with a smile. Osin didn't speak again.
"Exodus Deputy Commander! Exodus Commander!" Kollen's radio device called out. "We have detected a heat signature 20 degrees to our right front at 350 yards."
Kolom climbed onto the tank and put on his optical goggles. After switching to thermal imaging mode, he saw heat signatures in the distance.
"Yes, I see them," Kolom said into his throat microphone.
"Are they enemies?" Another recruit, Natalia, asked.
"Can't tell," Kolom said, turning on the microphone. "Exodus Platoon, don't fire unless attacked, first get them to come out."
As they came closer, the faint heat signatures transformed from blurred spots into clearer outlines. One of them ran towards somewhere, picked up something, and then ran back to the small hill. Then, these people crouched down and took up firing positions.
"We've encountered the enemy!" Captain Xiao shouted through the radio when orange tracer rounds were fired from the ridge. Bullets pinged against the side of the tank, and the assault team members jumped down from the tanks and took cover behind them. An anti-tank missile screamed through the air and slammed into the ground behind the tank formation, shrapnel hitting one of the tanks. Another missile struck the side of an APS-Cerberus armored vehicle and exploded. After the ammunition detonated, the crew members inside the armored vehicle scrambled out, seeking cover.
"Iron 1-2 and 1-3, 25 degrees to the right, 300 yards. Fire!" the tank platoon leader shouted through the radio. The main guns of Iron 1-2 and 1-3 fired, and shells screamed toward the ridge, sending dirt and debris flying into the air from the explosions.
"Send out the sentry robots!" Knox shouted while observing the ridge with a telescope. The rear door of a "Hound" opened, and a soldier without a weapon stepped out, wearing a specialized headset. He barked orders into a square microphone, and two "Sentry" robots responded. Their slender metal arms and legs moved forward, and they ran quickly. The robots were equipped with weapons, but they were all slung over their backs.
"Kill or capture?" Cress asked while observing.
"It looks like they want to capture them alive," Kollen guessed, watching as the two sentry robots disappeared into the ashes and smoke. Shouts and gunfire echoed from the ridge, but soon quieted down. After a while, the two sentry robots returned, dragging a person along, leaving a trail of boot prints on the ground. Upon reaching the safe area, the robots threw the prisoner to the ground, and he landed heavily in the mud and snow, groaning in pain.
He struggled to get up as Captain Xiao approached. Captain Xiao turned to one of the sentries. "How many?"
"Three dead, sir," the sentry robot replied. "The rest have fled on foot."
Captain Xiao nodded and turned to Kallen and Cress, who were standing nearby, and said, "Can the two of you take this person away?"
